#!/bin/ksh

# Access the build number
build_number="%system.build.number%"

# Get the current date in DD-MMM-YYYY format
current_date=$(date +"%d-%b-%Y")

# Create a unique ID with the current date and build number
unique_id="${current_date}_${build_number}"

# Print the unique ID for verification
echo "Generated Unique ID: $unique_id"

# Save the unique ID as a TeamCity build parameter
echo "##teamcity[setParameter name='env.UNIQUE_ID' value='$unique_id']"
This updated script uses the date command to get the current date in the "DD-MMM-YYYY" format and then concatenates it with the build_number to form the unique_id. The rest of the script remains the same, printing the unique ID and setting it as the UNIQUE_ID build parameter using the TeamCity service message ##teamcity[setParameter].





Regenerate
